    <h1> Pork Adobo Recipe </h1>
    <p> Traditional recipe of the Filipino pork adobo.</p>
    <h2>Ingredients</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>1kg pork belly</li>
      <li>1/2 cup soy sauce</li>
      <li>1/2 cup vinegar</li>
      <li>garlic</li>
      <li>black peper</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Instructions</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Heat the oil in a cooking pot</li>
      <li>Add the garlic. Cook until it starts to turn light brown</li>
      <li>Add the peppercorns. Continue to cook for 20 seconds so that its flavors get infused in the oil </li>
      <li>Put the pork belly in the cooking pot. Stir and cook until it turns light brown</li>
      <li>Pour the soy sauce and beef broth (or water). Let boil</li>
      <li> Cover and cook in low heat for 40 minutes or until the pork gets tender. Add more beef broth or water if the liquid starts to dry quickly</li>
      <li>Pour-in the vinegar. Let the liquid re-boil. Stir and cook for 8 minutes.</li>
      <li>Taste your pork adobo and decide to add salt if needed</li>
    </ol>
    <img src="https://www.kawalingpinoy.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/pork-adobo-1-3.jpg" alt="Pork Adobo">
